Below is a complete HTML file that implements a simple web app where users can input source code and receive random irritating nitpicky comments about it. The app is self-contained with embedded CSS and JavaScript.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Nitpicky Comment Generator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            color: #333;
        }
        h1 {
            text-align: center;
        }
        #codeInput {
            width: 100%;
            height: 200px;
            font-family: monospace;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }
        #generateComment {
            display: block;
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px;
            font-size: 16px;
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        #generateComment:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
        #comments {
            margin-top: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            background-color: white;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Nitpicky Comment Generator</h1>
    <textarea id="codeInput" placeholder="Paste your source code here..."></textarea>
    <button id="generateComment">Generate Nitpicky Comment</button>
    <div id="comments"></div>

    <script>
        const nitpickyComments = [
            "Variable names should be more descriptive. What's 'var1' supposed to mean?",
            "You really shouldn't have more than 3 levels of nested conditionals.",
            "Using global variables? Tsk, tsk. That could lead to unexpected behaviors.",
            "Your indentation is a bit off. Consistency is key!",
            "Why did you use a for loop when a map function would have sufficed?",
            "Maybe add some comments? Future you will thank you!",
            "You should really format your code for better readability.",
            "Why are you using alert? It's so outdated!",
            "This could have been a one-liner. Why so verbose?",
            "Did you even test this? It looks like a ticking time bomb!"
        ];

        document.getElementById('generateComment').addEventListener('click', function() {
            const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * nitpickyComments.length);
            const randomComment = nitpickyComments[randomIndex];
            document.getElementById('comments').innerText = randomComment;
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Instructions:
1. Copy the code above and paste it into a new `.html` file (e.g., `nitpickyCommentGenerator.html`).
2. Open the file in your web browser.
3. Paste some source code into the textarea and click the "Generate Nitpicky Comment" button to receive a random irritating comment about your code.
